from nigel allen subject library of congres to host dead sea scroll symposium april library of congres to host dead sea scroll symposium april to national and assignment desk daybook editor contact john sullivan or lucy suddreth both of the library of congres washington april a symposium on the dead sea scroll will be hold at the library of congres on wednesday april and thursday april the two-day program cosponsor by the library and baltimore hebrew university with additional support from the project judaica foundation will be hold in the library mumford room sixth floor madison building seating be limit and admission to any session of the symposium must be request in write see note a the symposium will be hold one week before the public open of a major exhibition scroll from the dead sea the ancient library of qumran and modern scholarship that open at the library of congres on april on view will be fragmentary scroll and archaeological artifact excavate at qumran on loan from the israel antiquity authority approximately item from library of congres special collection will augment these material the exhibition on view in the madison gallery through aug be make possible by a generou gift from the project judaica foundation of washington the dead sea scroll have be the focu of public and scholarly interest since when they be discover in the desert mile east of jerusalem the symposium will explore the origin and mean of the scroll and current scholarship scholar from diverse academic background and religiou affiliation will offer their disparate view ensure a lively discussion the symposium schedule include open remark on april at by librarian of congres jame h billington and by dr norma furst president baltimore hebrew university co-chairing the symposium be joseph baumgarten professor of rabbinic literature and institution baltimore hebrew university and michael grunberger head hebraic section library of congres geza verme professor emeritu of jewish study oxford university will give the keynote addres on the current state of scroll research focus on where we stand today on the second day the close addres will be give by shmaryahu talmon who will propose a research agenda pick up the theme of how the qumran study might proceed on wednesday april other speaker will include eugene ulrich professor of hebrew scripture university of notre dame and chief editor biblical scroll from qumran on the bible at qumran michael stone national endowment for the humanity distinguish visit professor of religiou study university of richmond on the dead sea scroll and the pseudepigrapha from to a special preview of the exhibition will be give to symposium participant and guest on thursday april begin at speaker will include magen broshi curator shrine of the book israel museum jerusalem on qumran the archaeological evidence p kyle mccarter albright professor of biblical and ancient near eastern study the john hopkin university on the copper scroll lawrence h schiffman professor of hebrew and judaic study new york university on the dead sea scroll and the history of judaism and jame vanderkam professor of theology university of notre dame on messianism in the scroll and in early christianity the thursday afternoon session at include devorah dimant associate professor of bible and ancient jewish thought university of haifa on qumran manuscript library of a jewish community norman golb rosenberger professor of jewish history and civilization oriental institute university of chicago on the current statu of the jerusalem origin of the scroll shmaryahu talmon magna professor emeritu of biblical study hebrew university jerusalem on the essential of the renewed covenant how should qumran study proceed will close the symposium there will be ample time for question and answer period at the end of each session also on wednesday april at the library of congres and the israel antiquity authority will hold a lecture by esther boyd-alkalay consult conservator israel antiquity authority on preserving the dead sea scroll in the mumford room jame madison memorial building the library of congres independence ave washington note a for more information about admission to the symposium please contact in write dr michael grunberger head hebraic section african and middle eastern division library of congres washington canada remote system toronto ontario 